{"title": "Human Boy And The War", "description": "Published in 1916, this is the third collection of thirteen humorous short stories about English school boys in a boarding school in the fictitious village Merivale. This book, of course, has World War I as a backdrop. Each story is told in the voice of a different boy at the school. The author wrote two other books in this series: The Human Boy (1900) and The Human Boy Again (1908). Eden Phillpotts was popular with the reading public and wrote prolifically novels, short stories, poetry, plays, and nonfiction. (David Wales)", "duration": 21563, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "2428", "name": "Eden Phillpotts"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/the_human_boy_and_the_war_1811_librivox/humanboywar_1811.jpg", "copyright_year": "1916", "genres": ["Single Author Collections"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "David Wales"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "David Wales"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "DaveC"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "DaveC"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "The Battle Of The Sand-Pit", "readers": [6454], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/the_human_boy_and_the_war_1811_librivox/humanboywar_01_phillpotts_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1779}, {"section": 2, "title": "The Mystery Of Fortescue", "readers": [6454], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/the_human_boy_and_the_war_1811_librivox/humanboywar_02_phillpotts_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1528}, {"section": 3, "title": "The Countrymen Of Kant", "readers": [6454], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/the_human_boy_and_the_war_1811_librivox/humanboywar_03_phillpotts_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1699}, {"section": 4, "title": "Travers Minor, Scout", "readers": [6454], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/the_human_boy_and_the_war_1811_librivox/humanboywar_04_phillpotts_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1616}, {"section": 5, "title": "The Hutchings Testimonial", "readers": [6454], "path": "http://www.archive.o